name: URLError.BackgroundTaskCancelledReason
desc: An enumeration of reasons used to explain the cancellation of a background task.

items.name: init?(rawValue: Int)
items.desc: Creates a background cancellation reason from the provided raw value.

items.name: case backgroundUpdatesDisabled
items.desc: A reason that indicates the system canceled the background task because background tasks are disabled.

items.name: case insufficientSystemResources
items.desc: A reason that indicates the system canceled the background task because it lacks sufficient resources to perform the task.

items.name: case userForceQuitApplication
items.desc: A reason that indicates the system canceled the background task because the user force-quit the application.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of this value by feeding them into the given hasher.

items.name: var rawValue: Int
items.desc: The raw value of this background cancellation reason instance.

items.name: typealias URLError.BackgroundTaskCancelledReason.RawValue
items.desc: The type of the raw value.

items.name: static func != (URLError.BackgroundTaskCancelledReason, URLError.BackgroundTaskCancelledReason) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two values are unequal.
